# Taldy-Bulak, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Taldy-Bulak (; , TaldÄ±bolaq) is a rural locality (a village) in Vosmomartovsky Selsoviet, Yermekeyevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 44 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Taldy-Bulak is located 72 km south of Yermekeyevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Novoshakovo is the nearest rural locality.
